<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Policy Path</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: black;
            color: white;
            font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif; /* Good choice for readability */
            display: flex; /* Use flexbox to center content */
            flex-direction: column; /* Stack elements vertically */
            align-items: center; /* Center horizontally */
            margin: 0; /* Remove default margin */
            text-align: center; /* Center text for headings */
            padding: 2%;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5em; /* Adjust font size as needed */
        }
        p {
            font-size: 0.9em; /* Smaller font size for the main paragraph */
            margin: 0.5em 0; /* Less space between lines */
        }
        h3 {
            margin: 0.5em 0; /* Less space between lines */
        }
        .direction {
            margin: 1em 0; /* Less space between directions */
            text-align: left; /* Align text to the left */
            width: 90%; /* Full width for left alignment */
            padding-left: 10%;
            padding-bottom: 2%;
        }
        .subdirection {
            margin: 0.7em 0; /* Less space between subdirections */
            list-style-type: disc; /* Bulleted list */
        }
        ul {
            padding-left: 20px; /* Indent bullets */
            margin: 0; /* Remove default margin */
        }
        a {
            margin-top: 1em; /* Space above the button */
            padding: 10px 20px; /* Button padding */
            background-color: #333; /* Dark background for the button */
            color: white; /* White text for the button */
            border: none; /* Remove border */
            border-radius: 5px; /* Rounded corners */
            cursor: pointer; /* Pointer cursor on hover */
            width: 25%;
            font-size: large;
            text-decoration: none; /* Remove underline */
            display: inline-block; /* To make padding and width work */
            text-align: center; /* Center text in the link */
            transition: background-color 0.3s; /* Smooth transition for color change */
        }
        a:hover {
            background-color: #555; /* Darker shade on hover */
        }
        a:active {
            background-color: #777; /* Change on click */
        }
    </style>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"> <!-- Import Google Font -->
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to Policy Path</h1>
    <p>A website that allows you to see the effects of climate change policies on climate change. Utilizing the NASA-powered ODIAC dataset, Policy Path is able to tell you the story and history of land carbon emissions for every place on Earth.</p>
    
    <h3 style="padding-top: 3%">Directions:</h3>
    <div class="direction">
        <p>1. Click anywhere on the Earth or type in a longitude and latitude.</p>
        <br>
        <p>2. See the story of climate change in that area, including:</p>
        <ul style="padding-left: 5%;">
            <li class="subdirection">A graph of land carbon emissions from 2000-2022.</li>
            <li class="subdirection">A year-by-year breakdown of emissions.</li>
            <li class="subdirection">A year-by-year breakdown and synopsis of regional policies passed to help the climate.</li>
            <li class="subdirection">A calculation of how the policies impacted carbon emissions.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <h3>By matching carbon emissions to regional policies, Policy Path makes it easy to understand which policies your region needs more of, and which policies cause more harm than good.</h3>
    <a id="startButton" href="/dash">Start</a> <!-- Changed to an <a> tag -->

</body>
</html>
